<CENTER>
<H2>Carol: A Day in a Girl's Life</H2>
<HR WIDTH="80%">
<H3>The Adventure Fantasy Animation</H3>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="ccover.jpg"><IMG SRC="ccover2.jpg" BORDER=1 WIDTH=250
HEIGHT=238 HSPACE=8 VSPACE=8 ALT="LD cover"></A>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<A HREF="ccover.jpg">[LD cover]</A>
</CENTER>

<BR>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=1 WIDTH="50%">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP><B>Genre:</B>
Shoujo/Fantasy/Music/Animated<BR>
<B>Type:</B> OAV (Original Animation Video)<BR>
<B>Year:</B> 1990<BR>
<B>Country:</B> Japan<BR>
<B>Language:</B> Japanese<BR>
<B>Runtime:</B> 60 minutes<BR>
<B>Laserdisc information:</B> T-Mue-Needs Inc. Movic. CBS/Sony Group Inc.
NTSC/Color. CLV/Stereo with Digital Audio. Catalogue number: CSLW 1234. 
6000 Yen (out of print).<BR>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<P><B>Carol</B> was originally a novel written by Naoto Kine, the guitarist of TM Network (aka TMN), a very famous J-pop band. The story was made into a one-shot OAV featuring character designs by shoujo manga artist Yun Kouga (of Earthian fame). The soundtrack, of course, was provided by TM Network.</P>

<P><B>Carol</B> is the story of a teenage girl whose life seems normal enough until she notices music disappearing from all around her, such as the sound of Big Ben, her father's cello-playing, and the concert of her favorite band, Gaball Screen. After hearing some mysterious voices, Carol is transported to a fantastic world where she must fight against the evil monsters who are stealing the music from Earth. She meets and is assisted by three dashing heroes: Clark, Tico, and Flash. These three are based on the members of TM Network. Clark is based on <A HREF="music.htm#komuro">Tetsuya "TK" Komuro</A>, the producer, songwriter, and keyboardist of TMN. Tico, with his characteristic sunglasses, is based on Naoto Kine. And finally, Flash is based on Takashi Utsunomiya, the lead singer of TMN.</P>

<P><B>Carol</B> is a pretty typical magical girl story. Its greatest strength is its excellent soundtrack by TMN, though the music seems to be underutilized at times. Casual viewers might find <B>Carol</B> uninspiring. However, for fans of TM Network, <B>Carol</B> is particularly fun to watch for its portrayals of TK, Naoto Kine, and Takashi Utsunomiya as Clark, Tico, and Flash.</P>

